a conjuring trick
trò ảo thuật

verb
-jures; -jured; -juring
[+ obj] to make (something) appear or seem to appear by using magic
a magician who conjures live doves from silk scarves
usually + up
In the movie she has the power to conjure up storms, fires, and earthquakes.
to make you think of (something)
The title of the book conjures [=evokes] images of politics, protest, and war.
usually + up
The photos conjure up memories of a simpler time.
For many, the word Greenland conjures up images of vast, icy plains.
to create or imagine (something)
The students conjured a clever scheme to raise the money they needed.
usually + up
Her imagination conjured up a summer scene.
a name to conjure with
chiefly Brit - used to say that someone is an important person
He has become a name to conjure with in the business world.
